<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="1166" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1166">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control
                                    (Italy)/7–2345</note>
                                <head>No. 1166<lb/><hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of
                                        State</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_DJC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dunn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                        the Secretary of the Soviet Delegation</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_NKV1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Novikov</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-27">July 27, 1945</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. <persName corresp="#p_NKV1">Novikov</persName></hi>: I refer to your note of July
                                    23, 1945<note n="1" xml:id="d1166fn1"><ref target="#d1164">Document No. 1164</ref>.</note> with which you enclosed
                                    an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> in regard to the British
                                    camp for Soviet citizens in the region of Cesenatico
                                    (Italy).</p>
                                <p>Since this is entirely a British matter I assume that you will
                                    approach the British separately and that your <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> was transmitted for information purposes
                                    only.</p>
                                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                                <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DJC1"><hi rend="smallcaps">James Clement
                                    Dunn</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>